Self Assessment – Noel Marenco

Code Quality and Functionality
The frontend code was implemented using React and organized into pages, components, and utility logic.
The code is structured to improve readability and reuse.

Main aspects of the code quality:
	•	Clear component structure
	•	Reusable form component
	•	Separation between UI and helper logic
	•	Basic error handling in form submission
	•	Routing for frontend pages

Challenges Faced
One of the main challenges was organizing the form logic correctly between components and utility files.
I also had to debug import issues and make sure the frontend matched the expected API structure.

What I Learned
From this project I learned:
	•	How to structure a React frontend for CRUD features
	•	How to separate components from utility logic
	•	How to handle form state with nested objects
	•	How to debug import and response handling issues
	•	How to use Git branches, commits, and rebasing in collaborative work

Overall, this project helped me improve my React structure, debugging, and teamwork workflow.
